post.body: Looks like you're the last one standing. I'm going to bed, tweet you tomorrow!
Good night Joe!
Have a good night!
I used to drink Pineapple Juice floats and pretend they were healthy. :-)
Have a good night!
Awww, so you're a fan of your wife? Even better. :-)
The Margaret Thatcher nutcracker is hilarious!!
It's a good thing I don't have vanilla ice cream, because a Coke float wouldn't be bad either!
Ugh. I had college friends that turned red from head to toe and it didn't slow them down...oh to be young and carefree again. :-)
Who knew? You're a Fanilow? ;-)
You know what would be even better with that? A splash of Bailey's!!
Sounds like a case of alcohol poisoning waiting to happen!
Good night!
Man, another person with great self-control. I'm surrounded! :-)
Negative calories since it has digestive enzymes to help break down the other calories you consumed! (sounds good to me)
Now THAT I would go for!
Night! Sleep well. Yeah, hubby always thinks he's going to sleep in, ends up waking up same time as for work. :-)
You're so good. I would have already had a bowl of ice cream in front of me. ;-)
Yep, it's huge!! And that Simply Organized shop looks interesting too. Have to get over there some time too.
Sounds like you had fun anyway! :-)
If you haven't been down that way for a while you will be shocked. There's a giant CostCo right across now!
I was wondering if you were coming here or to Waipio. We haven't even been to the one here. :-)
Congratulations!
I like a regular crust.
I like BBQ Chicken Pizza, but haven't tried the other types. Beer is great, but Coca-Cola goes with everything!
Aww, say it isn't true! We need your pep!
Shakey's building is now a Lone Star Steakhouse and they don't do line-dancing instead of karaoke now.
@cfnoble It's true about the anchovies, unless you're eating with a group of Filipinos like my friends that intro'd me to it.
Did you ever go there for karaoke? That's what it became near the end! Good memories of the pizza and chicken though. :-)
I don't mind pineapple and ham pizza, but not my favorite.
Peppermint Patty is a girl of course!
rofl, I had a feeling. ;-)
Question is, how did you do on the other 5?
I *love* anchovies on my pizza. :-)
Man, I wish 6 cheese pizzas could find their way to my door by themselves!
Have fun! Gil has a gig tonight otherwise I would join you all for dinner. :-)
Once again I let Twitter entertain me past my bedtime. I'll see all you folks tomorrow for more distraction and fun!
Yay! Good friend from waaaaay back just found me on Facebook. We rode the bus together in Junior High and High School!
RT @neenz: @FranMagbual We're going for the tweeple, food and music in that order :) -- That's how it should always be! #aloha09
